In [[toxicology]], the '''Lowest published toxic dose''' ('''Toxic Dose Low''', '''TD<sub>Lo</sub>''') is the lowest [[Dose (biochemistry)|dosage]] per unit of bodyweight (typically stated in [[milligram]]s per [[kilogram]]) of a [[Chemical substance|substance]] known to have produced signs of [[toxicity]] in a particular [[animal]] [[species]].  When quoting a TD<sub>Lo</sub>, the particular species and method of administration (''e.g.'' ingested, inhaled, [[intravenous]]) are typically stated.

