{{refimprove|date=January 2017}} {{Infobox academic division | name = San Diego State University College of Sciences | image = | image_size = | image_alt = | caption = | motto = | motto_lang = | motto_eng = | former_names = | established = | type = [[Public university|Public]] | parent = [[San Diego State University]] | city = [[San Diego]] | state = [[California]] | country = U.S. | coordinates = | dean = Walter Oechel (interim) | academic_staff = <!-- or |faculty= --> | students = 5,748<ref name=FastFacts>{{cite web |url=https://newscenter.sdsu.edu/mediarelations/fastfacts.aspx |title=Fast Facts |publisher=San Diego State University |accessdate=March 18, 2018}}</ref> | undergrad = 4,858<ref name=FastFacts/> | postgrad = 890<ref name=FastFacts/> | website = {{URL|www.sci.sdsu.edu}} | logo = }} The '''San Diego State University College of Sciences''' is the [[San Diego]] region's largest center for science education and research. Comprising eight departments and various specialties, the College offers [[bachelor's degree|bachelor's]], [[master's degree|master's]] and [[doctoral degree|doctoral]] degrees, as well as curricula for pre-professional students in medicine, veterinary medicine and dentistry. The College strives to produce scientifically educated graduates who possess both a fundamental understanding of their fields and the essential professional skills needed by local and regional industries. The College provides [[scientific literacy]] for all [[San Diego State University]] graduates as well as participating in the training of future mathematics and science teachers.
